comments: Walker's (BOS) arms are vertical when the contact to Lowry's (TOR) arm occurs during his driving shot attempt. Walker absorbs the oncoming body contact.
Lowry (TOR) briefly places a hand on Brown's (BOS) body as he begins his upward shooting motion during the jump shot attempt but Lowry immediately removes that hand. The contact is marginal.
Gasol (TOR) and Theis (BOS) both extend their arms for the rebound and each make marginal arm to arm contact.
Brown (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position and makes contact with the ball during Siakam's (TOR) driving shot attempt. Any ensuing contact to Siakam's arm is incidental.
VanVleet (TOR) and Theis (BOS) briefly engage and disengage during the screen.
Gasol (TOR) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Smart (BOS) and absorbs the contact to his front.
Walker (BOS) is moving along Lowry's (TOR) path when he makes contact with the ball and initiates some leg to leg contact simultaneously. The contact to Lowry's leg is marginal.
Theis (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position during VanVleet's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
Theis (BOS) jumps from point A to point B and he delivers contact to VanVleet's (TOR) body affecting his driving shot attempt.
Lowry (TOR) is in lane for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Brown (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position during Anunoby's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
